Archaic emblems are mysterious emblems that have been converted in favour of a new points system for Bounty Hunter. Only mysterious emblems that existed prior to 17 October 2019 will have been converted.

Players who have archaic emblems of any tier can give it to the Emblem Trader in exchange for old Bounty Hunter points, which can be used to purchase items from the Bounty Hunter Shop using the old points.

The old Bounty Hunter Store, which uses the old points system, will remain open for a couple of months after the full Bounty Hunter rework release to allow players ample time to cash in their archaic emblems and spend any remaining points.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
7 November 2019
(update)
  • With the release of the Bounty Hunter rework, archaic emblems are now discontinued, and will be removed alongside the old points system at an unannounced date.
  • The examine text was changed. Previously, it was "A mysterious emblem of ancient times, now superseded."
18 October 2019
 Hotfix

Archaic emblems were added back onto Wilderness Slayer drop tables until the Bounty Hunter rework is fully released.
